rComments: Awesome prof, course load is heavy so you have to put in work. If you put in work you can easily get a double digit mark

She was really good! Explained well, kept you interested and also initiated the use of twitter in this course! Attend her lectures because if you do, you really dont need to read the ebook, and study hard, you'll surely get a 85+! She's friendly, and very much approachable and  remembers you even if you visit her just once!

She attempts to kill you, her 1st midterm was fair, the 2nd was like a shower of gut wrenching, ball blasting bullets. Her final is like getting locked up in Auschwitz for 3 hours. It's just pain, horrible pain. To do well in this course pray to Allah, God, Vishnu, Krishna, Etc... that you were born with photographic memory. Goodbye, and goodnight
She explains things backwards, so that can be confusing. She gets really excited about her material and often screws up words. Focus on key words when studying. She is obsessed with those.
I simply adore her. She makes everything in the course interesting.Exams are very fair. Love this class :))
She taught the physiology portion of BIO210Y5. I think it was her first year teaching she did a decent job. Her short answer questions were very easy and her MC were ok.
